WEBVTT

00:06.006 --> 00:07.107 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF, PBS NEWSHOUR
ANCHOR: Good evening. I m Judy
Woodruff.

00:07.107 --> 00:08.809 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN, PBS NEWSHOUR
ANCHOR: And I m Hari
Sreenivasan.

00:08.809 --> 00:17.784 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: On the "NewsHour"
tonight, a new dynamic on the
campaign trail:

00:17.784 --> 00:27.327 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: Also ahead this
Thursday, no more e-cigarettes
for minors. The FDA announces

00:27.327 --> 00:31.832 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
new age requirements in a
crackdown on unregulated
tobacco, while California raises
the legal

00:31.832 --> 00:34.868 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
age for smoking to 21.

00:34.868 --> 00:39.940 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOODRUFF: And, planning a
vacation? How airlines are
battling over bargain passenger
fairs

00:39.940 --> 00:41.041 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
for trips to the Caribbean.

00:41.041 --> 00:42.676 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEIGN VIDEO CLIP)

00:42.676 --> 00:47.414 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
UNIDENTIFIED MALE: The airlines
are afraid that if customers are
given the choice, they'll

00:47.414 --> 00:50.984 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
buy their tickets somewhere else
from someone who will offer them
a better deal. The last

00:50.984 --> 00:51.952 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I heard, that was capitalism.

00:51.952 --> 00:53.654 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEO CLIP)

00:53.654 --> 01:01.028 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: All that and more
on tonight's "PBS NewsHour".

01:01.028 --> 01:06.300 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:06.300 --> 01:13.774 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Republican Donald
Trump gets back to campaigning
tonight, now that he's virtually

01:13.774 --> 01:19.913 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
wrapped up the GOP nomination
for president. But as he works
to win over voters, he faces

01:19.913 --> 01:25.352 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
new resistance from leaders in
his own party. The latest
example came today from Paul
Ryan,

01:25.352 --> 01:28.355 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
speaker of the House
of Representatives.

01:28.355 --> 01:32.326 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We begin our coverage with John
Yang, who's covering tonight's
Trump event in West Virginia.

01:32.326 --> 01:34.127 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEOTAPE)

01:34.127 --> 01:37.064 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JOHN YANG, PBS NEWSHOUR
CORRESPONDENT: For Donald Trump,
tonight's event in Charleston

01:37.064 --> 01:42.102 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
isn't about next week's primary,
it s all about winning the fall
campaign.

01:42.102 --> 01:47.207 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARK KEYSER: He come out, he won
Indiana, secured the nomination
and one of the first

01:47.207 --> 01:50.310 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
things that come out of his
mouth was we're going to help
people in West Virginia, we're

01:50.310 --> 01:54.548 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
going to help people in
Pennsylvania, we're going to get
coal back on the market.

01:54.548 --> 01:59.186 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
YANG: And in today's "New York
Times," Trump outlined goals for
his first 100 days in office.

01:59.186 --> 02:04.958 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They include: designing the wall
he says he'll build on the
Mexican border, stopping Muslim

02:04.958 --> 02:09.563 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
immigration, auditing the
Federal Reserve, and repealing
the Affordable Care Act.

02:09.563 --> 02:13.467 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He also went on CNBC, making
his economic pitch to voters.

02:13.467 --> 02:16.570 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP (R), PRESIDENTIAL
CANDIDATE: They have two jobs in
some cases, and they're

02:16.570 --> 02:21.041 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
making less money than they made
20 years ago. And that's why
you're wondering what's

02:21.041 --> 02:25.879 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
going on and why they're not
liking Republicans or Democrats.
I mean, they're not liking
either,

02:25.879 --> 02:28.281 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to be honest with you.

02:28.281 --> 02:33.120 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
YANG: But there's was new
evidence that Trump has a long
way to go to rally his own party

02:33.120 --> 02:38.992 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
behind him. House Speaker Paul
Ryan said today, he s not ready
to back Trump, and there

02:38.992 --> 02:42.462 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was more. "Politico" obtained a
recording of Republican Senator
John McCain speaking

02:42.462 --> 02:45.365 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
at a recent fundraiser.

02:45.365 --> 02:52.706 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SEN. JOHN MCCAIN (R), ARIZONA:
If Donald Trump is at the top of
the ticket, here in Arizona,

02:52.706 --> 02:55.742 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with over 30 percent of the vote
being the Hispanic vote, no
doubt that this may be the

02:55.742 --> 02:57.677 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
race of my life.

02:57.677 --> 03:01.481 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
YANG: Nevertheless, top Trump
aides have begun the behind the
scenes overtures to party
leaders.

03:01.481 --> 03:05.085 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
They've already had some
success. A number of Republican
members of Congress, are signing

03:05.085 --> 03:07.788 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
up to lend their support.

03:07.788 --> 03:12.726 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Meanwhile, the Democrats are
still battling. Bernie Sanders
is in West Virginia, too.

03:12.726 --> 03:15.028 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEN. BERNIE SANDERS (I-VT),
DEMOCRATIC PRESIDENTIAL
CANDIDATE: It's about time we
started in the

03:15.028 --> 03:17.864 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
wealthiest nation in the
world to talk about poverty.

03:17.864 --> 03:20.133 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(CHEERS)

03:20.133 --> 03:24.838 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
YANG: Still dogging Hillary
Clinton despite her big lead in
delegates.

03:24.838 --> 03:28.008 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Clinton already has Trump
squarely in her sights.

03:28.008 --> 03:31.211 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HILLARY CLINTON (D),
PRESIDENTIAL CANDIDATE: I think
that anybody running for office
should

03:31.211 --> 03:37.050 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
spend as much or more time
listening than talking and I
know I will be way ahead in

03:37.050 --> 03:40.387 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that category against Donald
Trump, there s no doubt about
that.

03:40.387 --> 03:43.090 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
YANG: She spent today
campaigning and fundraising in
California.

03:43.090 --> 03:45.692 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEOTAPE)

03:45.692 --> 03:51.098 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
YANG: People have been waiting
for hours in the cold rain in
Charleston, waiting for Donald

03:51.098 --> 03:57.003 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Trump to do what he says working
on Hillary Clinton, the
beginning of a general election

03:57.003 --> 04:01.241 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
campaign. A lot of the people
online say they re excited to
see Trump as the nominee for the

04:01.241 --> 04:04.211 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
very first time -- Judy.

04:04.211 --> 04:08.548 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: So, John, do you sense
there is something different in
how they see him now

04:08.548 --> 04:11.451 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
that he's the
presumptive nominee?

04:11.451 --> 04:15.822 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
YANG: I think there is
excitement that he's now the
guy, he has now cleared the way
to

04:15.822 --> 04:19.526 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the nomination and that he ll
start to take on Hillary
Clinton. A lot of the people we

04:19.526 --> 04:22.796 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
talked to said they were
very excited to see that.

04:22.796 --> 04:29.536 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A lot of talk here about West
Virginia. They hope he can help
West Virginia's economy,

04:29.536 --> 04:35.208 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
particularly the coal workers we
talked to, who were -- expressed
some anger at what they

04:35.208 --> 04:40.981 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
heard from Hillary Clinton
lately about putting coal
workers out of work, Judy.

04:40.981 --> 04:47.521 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: And, John, what have
you learned about how Donald
Trump may be shaping a different

04:47.521 --> 04:52.959 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
kind of campaign going into the
general election against
Secretary Clinton, assuming it
is

04:52.959 --> 04:54.795 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Secretary Clinton?

04:54.795 --> 04:59.799 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
YANG: Well, that's the big
question, Judy. These campaign
-- this campaign has been unlike

04:59.799 --> 05:05.105 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
anything we've ever seen before.
Not much television ads. A lot
of social media. A lot

05:05.105 --> 05:08.675 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
of free media.
Television interviews.

05:08.675 --> 05:13.747 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He only has one event a day,
usually late in the day like
this one because he's going

05:13.747 --> 05:19.653 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
home every night, commuting to
New York and flying out again
the next day. The big question

05:19.653 --> 05:23.256 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is whether this will change in
the general election, although
some may say you don t

05:23.256 --> 05:25.692 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
tinker with success -- Judy.

05:25.692 --> 05:30.830 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: And, finally, John, we
know that Hillary Clinton's
opponent Bernie Sanders

05:30.830 --> 05:36.403 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is also in West Virginia today.
Any read on the kind of
reception he's getting there?

05:36.403 --> 05:41.875 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
YANG: He s a pretty strong lead
in the polls, about 8-point lead
in the last pre-primary

05:41.875 --> 05:47.747 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
poll. And what's fueling his
campaign are a lot of the same
issues and the same forces

05:47.747 --> 05:54.621 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and the same demographics that
is giving Trump a lot of
strength here. This is a state
of

05:54.621 --> 06:02.996 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
poor white voters, a lot of whom
are hurting very much from the
economy, a lot of people

06:02.996 --> 06:08.235 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
hurting from the downturn in the
coal industry, a lot of those
things giving fuel to Sanders'

06:08.235 --> 06:12.405 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
campaign and it's also likely to
help him at some of the other
states down the road

06:12.405 --> 06:18.979 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
like Kentucky, right down until
that big showdown in California.

06:18.979 --> 06:24.184 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, he's going to be dogging
Hillary Clinton every step of
the way right to the end --
Judy.

06:24.184 --> 06:29.356 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: John Yang reporting
for us from what will be a Trump
campaign event in Charleston,

06:29.356 --> 06:30.490 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
West Virginia -- we thank you.

06:30.490 --> 06:33.793 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
YANG: Thanks, Judy.

06:33.793 --> 06:38.331 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: We'll take a closer
look at how Republicans are
dividing over Donald Trump

06:38.331 --> 06:41.835 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
as their nominee a little
later in the program.

06:41.835 --> 06:46.039 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: In the day's other
news, a raging wildfire forced
new evacuations in the heart

06:46.039 --> 06:51.511 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of Canada's oil sands country.
Wind-driven flames had already
put more than 80,000 people

06:51.511 --> 06:56.883 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to flight, from Fort McMurray in
Alberta. There were more towns
to the south that were

06:56.883 --> 07:00.453 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
evacuated as the fire swept
across tinder-dry woodlands.

07:00.453 --> 07:02.155 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Paul Davies of Independent
Television News has this report.

07:02.155 --> 07:03.790 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEOTAPE)

07:03.790 --> 07:06.793 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
PAUL DAVIES, INDEPENDENT
TELEVISION NEWS: They are
driving away from homes they
have

07:06.793 --> 07:13.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
abandoned to the flames. The
fire so close, it's showering
sparks from trees it's consuming

07:13.266 --> 07:18.138 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
alongside the road. And caught
in this vision of Armageddon,
thousands of families running

07:18.138 --> 07:21.041 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
for their lives.

07:21.041 --> 07:27.580 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How long it will be before Fort
McMurray will welcome people
again, no one can know.

07:27.580 --> 07:32.852 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The city had laid on a fleet of
buses to help the less
advantaged escape from the
inevitable

07:32.852 --> 07:36.856 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
destruction, but there were
strict limits on what
possessions could be taken. For
many,

07:36.856 --> 07:40.593 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it was the clothes they could
carry and their pets but no
more.

07:40.593 --> 07:44.397 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONNA GOALLAMOT, EVACUEE: You
don't know what's burned and
what s not burned, when you can

07:44.397 --> 07:50.704 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
go back. Now you're sitting here
and all you see is red flames.
It's pretty scary.

07:50.704 --> 07:55.942 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVIES: The evacuation so far
prevented loss of life but in
the suburbs where the flames

07:55.942 --> 08:00.980 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have done their worse and moved
on, there is little left for
people to return to.

08:00.980 --> 08:05.418 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Two thousand buildings have been
destroyed and tonight there are
fears large portions

08:05.418 --> 08:08.288 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the city may be lost before
any improvement in weather
conditions.

08:08.288 --> 08:11.124 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEOTAPE)

08:11.124 --> 08:16.029 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: The fire has also
shut down about one-third of
Canada's total crude oil
capacity.

08:16.029 --> 08:22.569 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: A near- miracle today
in Nairobi, Kenya. Four more
people were rescued after

08:22.569 --> 08:27.207 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
being trapped for six days in
the rubble of a collapsed
building. The first was a woman

08:27.207 --> 08:31.945 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
who was eight months pregnant
and was taken to a nearby
hospital for treatment.
Officials

08:31.945 --> 08:36.549 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
said her unborn baby did not
survive. The death toll from
Friday's collapse now stands

08:36.549 --> 08:40.253 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
at 36, with dozens
still missing.

08:40.253 --> 08:45.125 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: In Syria, an air
strike killed at least 28 people
in a crowded refugee camp,

08:45.125 --> 08:50.063 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
including children. It happened
at the northwestern town of
Sarmada, in a rebel-held area
near

08:50.063 --> 08:54.934 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Turkish border. Video posted
on social media showed tents
burned to the ground, amid

08:54.934 --> 09:00.373 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
clouds of dark smoke. The camp
is home to around 2,000 people.
It was unclear whose

09:00.373 --> 09:04.744 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
planes carried out the strike,
but U.S. officials denied any
role.

09:04.744 --> 09:09.682 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Meanwhile, the prime
minister of Turkey announced
today he's resigning, moving

09:09.682 --> 09:16.256 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the NATO nation ever closer to
authoritarian rule. Ahmet
Davutoglu had held his office

09:16.256 --> 09:22.629 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
since 2014, but he was at odds
with President Recep Tayyip
Erdogan, who's pushing for
greater

09:22.629 --> 09:27.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
power for himself. Even so, the
prime minister pledged continued
support for Erdogan, despite

09:27.967 --> 09:29.269 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
his crackdown on dissent.

09:29.269 --> 09:31.738 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEO CLIP)

09:31.738 --> 09:35.842 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AHMET DAVUTOGLU, PRIME MINISTER,
TURKEY (translated): My loyalty
to our president will continue

09:35.842 --> 09:40.613 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
until the last breath I will
breathe. Nobody has or will hear
a single word against our

09:40.613 --> 09:43.550 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
president from my mouth.
Everybody should know that and I
would never let people exploit

09:43.550 --> 09:44.384 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
this matter.

09:44.384 --> 09:46.619 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEO CLIP)

09:46.619 --> 09:51.391 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: The resignation comes
as Europe is relying on Turkey
to cut off the flow of

09:51.391 --> 09:56.296 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
migrants, and the U.S. needs its
help fighting the Islamic state
group.

09:56.296 --> 09:59.799 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: Back in this
country, the number of sexual
assaults reported in the
military

09:59.799 --> 10:04.070 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
stayed about the same last year,
but Pentagon officials say it's
still far too high. In

10:04.070 --> 10:10.977 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
all, there were 6,083 reports of
assaults in 2015, virtually
unchanged from 2014. At

10:10.977 --> 10:15.148 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the same time, more than 16,000
service members intervened in
situations they believed could

10:15.148 --> 10:18.384 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
escalate to sexual assault.

10:18.384 --> 10:24.824 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: President Obama has
commuted prison sentences for 58
more federal convicts. It's

10:24.824 --> 10:29.929 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
part of his recent push to
overhaul the criminal justice
system, with a focus on
non-violent

10:29.929 --> 10:34.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
drug offenders. Most of this
latest group will be freed in
September. 18 had been serving

10:34.667 --> 10:37.203 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
life sentences.

10:37.203 --> 10:40.974 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
SREENIVASAN: Wall Street
struggled to find much direction
today. The Dow Jones Industrial

10:40.974 --> 10:45.211 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Average gained nine points to
close at 17,660, the NASDAQ fell
eight points, and the S&amp;P

10:45.211 --> 10:48.281 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
500 dropped a
fraction of a point.

10:48.281 --> 10:54.554 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: And, a game that dates
back to 1978 leads the new class
of inductees into the

10:54.554 --> 11:01.961 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Video Game Hall of Fame. "Space
Invaders" set off a craze for
arcade games in the '70s

11:01.961 --> 11:07.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and '80s. Also inducted today:
the educational adventure game
"Oregon Trail," as well as

11:07.767 --> 11:13.673 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
"Sonic The Hedgehog," "The
