him but worry as president he
doesn't have the temperament to
be leader of the free world.

22:07.193 --> 22:11.830 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARINO: Well, if he didn't have
the temperament to be the
president, I don't think he
would

22:11.830 --> 22:17.937 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
be as successful as he is in
business. I have been with him
many times, smoking with him

22:17.937 --> 22:22.374 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
many times. He asked my
advice. I give it to him.

22:22.374 --> 22:27.346 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I don't say just exactly what
you might want to hear because
I m that kind of a person,

22:27.346 --> 22:31.116 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but just look in the past. What
has -- what does Hillary Clinton
have to offer? You know,

22:31.116 --> 22:37.389 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
what do other candidates have to
offer as far as creating jobs?

22:37.389 --> 22:42.261 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's known all over the world
and he's certainly going to let
the rest of the world know that

22:42.261 --> 22:45.798 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we don't think we're better than
anyone else, but we re not going
to be taken advantage

22:45.798 --> 22:51.403 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of anymore like we have been in
trade, like we have been in
foreign affairs concerning

22:51.403 --> 22:56.642 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Putin. He's going to take China
on. I think they know that he's
a serious guy and I believe

22:56.642 --> 23:01.947 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that he's going to make this
country great again with the
help of the American people.

23:01.947 --> 23:06.085 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: And what do you say to
the leader in your own party in
the House of Representatives,

23:06.085 --> 23:10.422 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Speaker Paul Ryan, who said
today he's not ready to support
Donald Trump because he still

23:10.422 --> 23:14.260 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
has work to do to
unify your party?

23:14.260 --> 23:20.532 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARINO: Well, Paul is new at the
job. It's a big switch going
from the chairman over

23:20.532 --> 23:25.504 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to the speaker of the House
because there is no one in the
public's eye than the speaker

23:25.504 --> 23:28.674 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
other than the president.

23:28.674 --> 23:33.846 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I'm going to give Paul the
benefit of the doubt. We're back
in D.C. next week. We'll

23:33.846 --> 23:39.985 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have a discussion about that.
There it is a responsibility
there that he has to work

23:39.985 --> 23:44.590 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to bring the party together and
I know he and Donald have been
having discussions.

23:44.590 --> 23:47.960 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Representative Tom
Marino of Pennsylvania, we thank
you very much.

23:47.960 --> 23:51.196 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MARINO: It's always my pleasure.

23:51.196 --> 23:56.168 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: And Donald Trump has
responded to Speaker Ryan this
evening. In his statement,

23:56.168 --> 24:01.573 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he said, quote, "I am not ready
to support Speaker Ryan's
agenda. Perhaps in the future

24:01.573 --> 24:06.779 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we can work together and come to
an agreement about what is best
for the American people.

24:06.779 --> 24:10.349 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They have been treated so badly
for so long that it's about time
for politicians to put

24:10.349 --> 24:13.319 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
them first."

24:13.319 --> 24:18.090 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Now for a view from a
conservative critic of Donald
Trump, we turn to John
McCormack,

24:18.090 --> 24:20.559 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
senior writer at "The
Weekly Standard" magazine.

24:20.559 --> 24:23.128 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
John McCormack, welcome.

24:23.128 --> 24:27.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Why are you opposed to Mr.
Trump as the party's nominee?

24:27.166 --> 24:29.968 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN MCCORMACK, THE WEEKLY
STANDARD: Well, you know, what
you heard Paul Ryan say today

24:29.968 --> 24:34.873 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is that we want a standard
bearer who bears our standards.
And you could view that from

24:34.873 --> 24:38.610 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
one respect as a matter of
ideology, something that Paul
Ryan would say is that we're
going

24:38.610 --> 24:41.747 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to have a debt crisis if we
don't get entitlements under
control, Donald Trump is
completely

24:41.747 --> 24:44.817 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
not a conservative on that
and many other issues.

24:44.817 --> 24:49.121 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But for me, really, the issue is
more of temperament and
character. I think that for the
past ten

24:49.121 --> 24:53.759 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
months, Donald Trump has proven
to be nothing less than an
unstable conspiracy theorist

24:53.759 --> 24:57.963 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with an authoritarian streak.
You know, he has -- he got his
start in politics saying

24:57.963 --> 25:03.135 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Barack Obama's birth certificate
was fake. He suggests that
George W. Bush knowingly

25:03.135 --> 25:07.206 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
lied that there are weren't
weapons of mass destruction in
Iraq. That s an unproven

25:07.206 --> 25:11.643 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
conspiracy theory. Just this
week, he said that Ted Cruz's
father was involved in the

25:11.643 --> 25:13.545 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JFK assassination.

25:13.545 --> 25:18.050 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That s just sheer lunacy, and it
doesn t, it s not the kind of
stability that you

25:18.050 --> 25:22.054 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
want in a commander-in-chief.
So, for me, I d be willing to
take a chance on Donald

25:22.054 --> 25:25.424 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Trump, if you just simply want
quite (ph) as conservatives I
like. But again, on matters

25:25.424 --> 25:28.260 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of character and temperament, I
just don't think he's there.

25:28.260 --> 25:34.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Well, you probably
heard, I talked with Congressman
Tom Marino of Pennsylvania,

25:34.900 --> 25:39.571 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who I asked him that temperament
question, and he said, well,
he's been a successful

25:39.571 --> 25:41.807 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
businessman. He said his
temperament is what's helped him
get him where he is today. What

25:41.807 --> 25:44.042 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
about that?

25:44.042 --> 25:47.813 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MCCORMACK: Well, if you look at
a lot of his business dealings,
you know, he's really just

25:47.813 --> 25:53.819 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
insulted a lot of people, been
very aggressive. He's gotten
where he is more out of his fame

25:53.819 --> 26:00.025 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
than business acumen. I mean,
just in his campaign, we've seen
him denigrate women,

26:00.025 --> 26:04.430 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he has insulted even prisoners
of war when he said of John
McCain, tat I like people

26:04.430 --> 26:08.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
who weren't captured. I can't
believe a patriotic party has
chosen someone who has
denigrated

26:08.100 --> 26:10.302 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
prisoners of war like that.

26:10.302 --> 26:13.439 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And until Donald Trump can prove
he's a man of character and a
man of temperament, which

26:13.439 --> 26:16.775 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he hasn t done, which I don't
think he can do, I can t support
him.

26:16.775 --> 26:20.979 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Are you saying you
don t think you could come
around -- you and others who

26:20.979 --> 26:25.851 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
agree with you, couldn't come
around to support Donald Trump
if he demonstrates temperament

26:25.851 --> 26:30.489 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
you say you look for in a
president changes and maybe
comes up with positions on
issues

26:30.489 --> 26:32.825 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
that you can agree with?

26:32.825 --> 26:35.894 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MCCORMACK: Well, I think the
Donald Trump that we've seen
over the last ten months is

26:35.894 --> 26:41.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the real Donald Trump. I don't
see him, you know, apologizing
publicly to all the women

26:41.266 --> 26:46.038 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he's insulted -- degraded,
really -- to the prisoner of war
people like John McCain, to

26:46.038 --> 26:51.643 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
excommunicate the nationalists
who have found a welcoming home
in his campaign, to prove

26:51.643 --> 26:54.880 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that he has a sober and steady
hands. You know, I mean, he
bounces all over the place

26:54.880 --> 26:58.617 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on tissues. He can't control his
worst impulses, as he insults
Heidi Cruz, he threatened to,

26:58.617 --> 27:01.620 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
quote, "spill the beans" on her.

27:01.620 --> 27:04.656 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It s not the stability you re
seeing, and I think the person
you've seen in the

27:04.656 --> 27:08.026 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
last ten months is the real
Donald Trump. So, I don't think
I'll be able to support

27:08.026 --> 27:12.197 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
him in November. I hope there is
a third party candidate, maybe
somebody like Dr. Coburn

27:12.197 --> 27:15.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from Oklahoma. Time is running
out to get on the ballot, but I
hope there's a viable

27:15.367 --> 27:18.170 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
option for principled
conservatives in November.

27:18.170 --> 27:21.106 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Well, that s what I
want to ask you, John McCormack.
What do you and other

27:21.106 --> 27:26.345 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
conservatives do who aren't able
to support Donald Trump? If you
support a third party,

27:26.345 --> 27:31.183 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
doesn't that automatically help
the Democratic nominee who's
likely to be Hillary Clinton?

27:31.183 --> 27:34.186 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MCCORMACK: Well, you know, the
polls show right now that
Hillary Clinton is going to

27:34.186 --> 27:38.257 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
beat Donald Trump whether or not
conservative. It's very likely
she'll beat him whether or

27:38.257 --> 27:43.562 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
not conservatives support Donald
Trump. A recent CNN poll found
84 percent of Republican

27:43.562 --> 27:47.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
back Donald Trump. Hillary
Clinton was leading Trump
overall by 13 percentage points,
which

27:47.266 --> 27:50.636 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
means if you have 100 percent of
Republicans supported Donald
Trump, he would still lose

27:50.636 --> 27:53.038 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to Hillary Clinton.

27:53.038 --> 27:56.542 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, you know, at the end of the
day, conservatives, they just
kind of take a stand and say
that

27:56.542 --> 28:00.746 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
they believe that both
candidates are disqualified. On
one hand, you see Hillary
Clinton, someone

28:00.746 --> 28:04.750 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who s Supreme Court nominee
would trample the Constitution,
send the country hurdling

28:04.750 --> 28:09.187 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to the left, and then Donald
Trump, who as I said, is simply
unfit to be commander-in-chief.

28:09.187 --> 28:12.324 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And you just have to take a
stand, let the chips fall where
they may. You can hope that

28:12.324 --> 28:14.459 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
there is a third party
principled candidate there and
if not, write somebody in and
vote

28:14.459 --> 28:16.762 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
down ballot.

28:16.762 --> 28:19.998 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: I want to ask you
about another point that we
heard Congressman Marino make,

28:19.998 --> 28:21.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and that is, he said Trump
appeals -- he s a populist. He s
appealing to Democrats,

28:21.466 --> 28:21.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to independents, as well as
Republicans. Why wouldn't Donald
Trump be able to put together

28:21.600 --> 28:23.268 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
a coalition that could
prevail in November?

28:23.268 --> 28:23.969 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF, PBS NEWSHOUR
ANCHOR: I want to ask you about
another point that we heard

28:23.969 --> 28:24.503 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Congressman Marino make, and
that is, he said Trump appeals
-- he s a populist. He s

28:24.503 --> 28:29.007 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
appealing to Democrats, to
independents, as well as
Republicans. Why wouldn't Donald
Trump

28:29.007 --> 28:33.545 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
be able to put together a
coalition that could prevail in
November?

28:33.545 --> 28:36.415 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN MCCORMACK, THE WEEKLY
STANDARD: Well, it hasn't
happened so far. He has the
highest

28:36.415 --> 28:41.587 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
unfavorable ratings of any
candidate in the modern era.
Roughly 65 percent of Americans

28:41.587 --> 28:47.759 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have an unfavorable view of him.
His net unfavorability rating is
minus 37 percent, Hillary
Clinton

28:47.759 --> 28:52.230 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is minus 17. So, she's not all
that unpopular but he's a lot
more unpopular than she is.

28:52.230 --> 28:56.068 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He would have to be a different
person in the next six months to
have people have a

28:56.068 --> 28:59.371 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
different view of him. I m not
sure he's capable of that. I
highly doubt it.

28:59.371 --> 29:03.542 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: So, just quickly, you
don't see the Republican Party
and conservatives coming

29:03.542 --> 29:07.346 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
together between now and
November to support him?

29:07.346 --> 29:11.350 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MCCORMACK: I think a lot of
principled conservatives simply
won't be able to. I don't think
that

29:11.350 --> 29:16.288 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
the fact he's now the
presumptive nominee doesn't
change the fact he's manifestly
unfit

29:16.288 --> 29:19.791 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to be president of the United
States and commander-in-chief,
and neither do I think Hillary
Clinton is

29:19.791 --> 29:23.662 align:left position:25%,start line:73.33% size:75%
qualified to be
commander-in-chief, given what
her Supreme Court nominees would
do to

29:23.662 --> 29:26.632 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the Constitution and where
they would take this country.

29:26.632 --> 29:29.701 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: John McCormack, senior
writer for "The Weekly Standard"
magazine -- thank you

29:29.701 --> 29:32.537 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
very much.

29:32.537 --> 29:35.874 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MCCORMACK: Thank you.

29:35.874 --> 29:38.243 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
