37:36.254 --> 37:43.394 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: The tense state of
relations between the U.S. and
Saudi Arabia has been

37:43.394 --> 37:48.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
roiled lately by two issues: a
pending bill in Congress that
would allow lawsuits against

37:48.766 --> 37:54.672 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
countries found to have been
involved in terrorist attacks on
American soil, and the so-called

37:54.672 --> 37:59.244 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
"28 pages," parts of a
congressional inquiry after
September 11th that are said to
detail

37:59.244 --> 38:03.281 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
possible Saudi complicity
in aiding the attacks.

38:03.281 --> 38:07.118 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Here to tell us more about both
is chief foreign affairs
correspondent Margaret Warner.

38:07.118 --> 38:10.355 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, first, let's talk about the
bill, what's in it and what's
the status of it.

38:10.355 --> 38:12.457 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER, PBS CHIEF
FOREIGN AFFAIRS CORRSPONDENT:
The bill, Hari, would carve

38:12.457 --> 38:17.428 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
out a special exemption in
what's called the Foreign
Sovereign Immunity Act which
every

38:17.428 --> 38:22.934 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
country has a similar act and
observe, which is you don't sue
foreign governments, with

38:22.934 --> 38:27.772 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a few narrow exceptions. There
was an exception made for
terrorism, but only if you were
on

38:27.772 --> 38:31.743 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the state-sponsored terrorism
list which Saudi isn't.

38:31.743 --> 38:39.250 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, these 9/11 victims families
have been trying to push this,
get this bill in a court.

38:39.250 --> 38:44.722 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was rejected by a federal
judge in September saying,
sorry, violates this act. So
that's

38:44.722 --> 38:48.359 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
sort of what's new here.

38:48.359 --> 38:53.464 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It passed unanimously a session
ago in the Senate, but now, it's
run into a buzz saw

38:53.464 --> 38:57.936 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of White House opposition. You
have President Obama telling
Charlie Rose if we let this

38:57.936 --> 39:03.708 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
happen we'll have foreign
citizens suing our government.
All the senior members of the

39:03.708 --> 39:06.344 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
administration have
come out against this.

39:06.344 --> 39:11.583 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, and then, last -- two weeks
ago, Senator Lindsey Graham, one
of the 22 co-sponsors

39:11.583 --> 39:18.156 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and lawyer by training put a
hold on the bill. So, people
thought it was dead. But several

39:18.156 --> 39:23.528 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
widows came to see him last
week. He was working on
language. And today, I learned
very quietly

39:23.528 --> 39:26.864 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
he removed his hold on Tuesday.

39:26.864 --> 39:31.736 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, what's happening now is that
the two main co-sponsors,
Republican John Cornyn and
Democrat

39:31.736 --> 39:37.475 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Chuck Schumer of New York are
essentially counting heads. They
want to make sure nobody

39:37.475 --> 39:42.280 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in their caucus objects, no one
else is going to put a secret
hold on it, and then they ll

39:42.280 --> 39:45.350 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ask Mitch Zeller if he will
bring it to the floor.

39:45.350 --> 39:51.556 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: What role do the 28
pages play in this. They're
discrete but melt together.

39:51.556 --> 39:58.229 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WARNER: Yes, they do. And a lot
is sort of a public relations
side. A White House official

39:58.229 --> 40:03.635 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
said to me that "60 Minutes"
report that appeared, what,
three weeks ago in which the
head of

40:03.635 --> 40:09.707 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the congressional investigation,
co-sponsor Bob Graham, and three
of the 9/11 Commission

40:09.707 --> 40:16.114 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
members, which you know was an
independent, came out and said
there is very -- they didn't

40:16.114 --> 40:21.386 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
say "evidence" but strong signs
of Saudi complicity in aiding
some of the hijackers -- as we
recall

40:21.386 --> 40:26.157 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
15 of the 19 were Saudis -- and
in particular the two who were
in San Diego.

40:26.157 --> 40:30.695 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, mysteriously, they
meet a man who gives them an
apartment, and these are two

40:30.695 --> 40:35.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
guys who don't speak any English
and have had no experience
living in the West. So,

40:35.166 --> 40:41.673 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
there are a lot of threads in
there. What one White House
official said is that "60

40:41.673 --> 40:47.178 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Minutes" report has been like is
that rocket has been a booster
to the Saudi lawsuit bill.

40:47.178 --> 40:51.015 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And a top staffer of one of the
senators involved said much the
same. He said, we were kind

40:51.015 --> 40:54.986 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of bumping along on the Saudi
lawsuit bill, and suddenly, it's
front and center.

40:54.986 --> 40:57.989 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: Likely to turn into
a presidential campaign issue?

40:57.989 --> 41:03.294 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WARNER: Well, maybe. The thing
is that both Hillary Clinton and
Donald Trump have actually

41:03.294 --> 41:10.468 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
endorsed the Saudi lawsuit bill
and especially when they were in
New York and on New York

41:10.468 --> 41:16.541 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
radio and television. So, I
don t -- I think the only thing
that could become political

41:16.541 --> 41:20.745 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is if President Obama, who is
supposed to decide on the 28
pages, supposedly by the

41:20.745 --> 41:25.483 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
end of next month, if he were to
say I m not releasing them, then
it could be an issue.

41:25.483 --> 41:28.052 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: What's the White
House's reaction been to all
this?

41:28.052 --> 41:34.158 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WARNER: Oh, the White House is
apoplectic. And the way one
senior, very senior official

41:34.158 --> 41:37.962 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
just before the president was
going to Saudi Arabia, he said
this is the last thing we

41:37.962 --> 41:41.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
need. The Saudis are violently
opposed to this. They say they
don t mind releasing

41:41.833 --> 41:48.439 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
28 pages, but they feel they re
being absolutely, you know, put
in the crosshairs on this bill

41:48.439 --> 41:55.246 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and, in fact, at one point, the
foreign minister threatened to
sell all of their assets,
foreign

41:55.246 --> 42:00.418 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
assets, 750 billion on the
market. He since rescinded that
but still they are very
concerned.

42:00.418 --> 42:05.423 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: Chief White House
correspondent Margaret Warner,
thanks so much.

42:05.423 --> 42:11.763 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
WARNER: Thank you.

42:11.763 --> 42:18.336 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Now, looking back and
looking anew at an artist at the
center of the so-called

42:18.336 --> 42:22.073 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
"culture wars" of
the 1980s and '90s.

42:22.073 --> 42:22.907 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Jeffrey Brown reports
from Los Angeles.

42:22.907 --> 42:24.809 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
